  failure locally, and resolve the specific issue.</shortdesc>

  <troublebody class="- topic/body troubleshooting/troublebody " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/troubleshooting/ts_ci-fails.dita" xtrc="troublebody:1;27:16">

    <condition id="condition" class="- topic/section troubleshooting/condition " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/troubleshooting/ts_ci-fails.dita" xtrc="condition:1;29:31">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/troubleshooting/ts_ci-fails.dita" xtrc="title:2;30:14">Situation</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/troubleshooting/ts_ci-fails.dita" xtrc="p:1;31:10">Your pull request shows a failing check in CI. The check is named
      something like <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/troubleshooting/ts_ci-fails.dita" xtrc="b:1;32:25">Validate documentation</b> or <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/troubleshooting/ts_ci-fails.dita" xtrc="b:2;32:58">validate</b>. The
      merge button is blocked.</p>
    </condition>

